<subSubSection lastPageId="53" lastPageNumber="54" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="52.[151,1436,1798,2003]" box="[199,1436,1978,2003]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1979,2003]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Collins, M. J. &amp; Jones, D. A. &amp; Clayton, D. A." box="[324,554,1978,2003]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="318 - 328" refId="ref46387" refString="Collins, M. J., Jones, D. A. &amp; Clayton, D. A. (1984) Redescription of Uca sindensis (Alcock, 1900) (Brachyura: Ocypodidae) with notes on the ecology of a population from Kuwait. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 4 (2), 318 - 328, figs. 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1984">
Collins 
<emphasis box="[413,463,1979,2003]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">et al</emphasis>
. (1984)
</bibRefCitation>
recorded this species from 
<collectingCountry box="[872,917,1979,2002]" name="Iran" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Iran</collectingCountry>
in the northern Persian Gulf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Apel, M. &amp; Turkay, M." box="[1261,1436,1978,2002]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="131 - 142" refId="ref45263" refString="Apel, M., &amp; Turkay, M. (1999) Taxonomic Composition, Distribution and Zoogeographic Relationships of the Grapsid and Ocypodid Crab Fauna of Intertidal Soft Bottoms in the Persian Gulf. Estuarine, Coastal and Shelf Science, 49 (Supplement A), 131 - 142" type="journal article" year="1999">Apel &amp; Türkay</bibRefCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1436,151,428]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
(1999) mentioned that the specimen recorded by 
<bibRefCitation author="Collins, M. J. &amp; Jones, D. A. &amp; Clayton, D. A." box="[741,984,151,176]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="318 - 328" refId="ref46387" refString="Collins, M. J., Jones, D. A. &amp; Clayton, D. A. (1984) Redescription of Uca sindensis (Alcock, 1900) (Brachyura: Ocypodidae) with notes on the ecology of a population from Kuwait. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 4 (2), 318 - 328, figs. 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1984">
Collins 
<emphasis box="[835,890,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">et al</emphasis>
. (1984)
</bibRefCitation>
was deposited in the Natural History Museum of London is actually from the Gulf of 
<collectingCountry box="[697,769,188,212]" name="Oman" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Oman</collectingCountry>
. Beinlich &amp; von Hagen (2006) introduced a new subgenus, namely 
<emphasis box="[240,338,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Cranuca</emphasis>
for this species which is considered of being part of an ancestral base for wide-front fiddler crabs which is characterized by combining a wide front and lacking a pleonal clasping apparatus. This species is common in the Red Sea, living sympatrically with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kossmann" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[616,774,296,320]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Uca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albimana">
<emphasis box="[616,774,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Uca albimana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
along muddy shores and mangroves. Both of these species have been recorded from the south-western Persian Gulf along the coast of the 
<collectingCountry box="[1050,1107,332,356]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">UAE</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Apel, M. &amp; Turkay, M." box="[1123,1366,332,356]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="131 - 142" refId="ref45263" refString="Apel, M., &amp; Turkay, M. (1999) Taxonomic Composition, Distribution and Zoogeographic Relationships of the Grapsid and Ocypodid Crab Fauna of Intertidal Soft Bottoms in the Persian Gulf. Estuarine, Coastal and Shelf Science, 49 (Supplement A), 131 - 142" type="journal article" year="1999">Apel &amp; Türkay 1999</bibRefCitation>
). This record shows that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hoffman" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[355,471,368,392]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Uca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inversa">
<emphasis box="[355,375,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">U</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[389,471,368,391]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">inversa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distributed northward, now colonizing in 
<collectingCountry box="[943,1022,367,391]" name="Iran" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Qeshm</collectingCountry>
I., whereas 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kossmann" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[1159,1299,368,392]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Uca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albimana">
<emphasis box="[1159,1179,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">U</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1193,1299,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">albimana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the south-western part of the Persian Gulf.
</paragraph>
